# llms.mda — Site-Level AI Guidance

This example demonstrates how MAGI can serve as a richer alternative to `llms.txt` for providing site-level context to AI systems.

## Site Overview

This is the documentation site for MAGI (Markdown for Agent Guidance & Instruction). MAGI extends standard Markdown with structured metadata, embedded AI instructions, and explicit document relationships.

## Key Pages

| Page | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `/docs/introduction` | What MAGI is and why it exists |
| `/docs/specification` | Full technical specification |
| `/docs/quickstart` | Get started in 5 minutes |
| `/docs/developer-guide` | Encoding and decoding MAGI documents |
| `/docs/architecture` | How MAGI components fit together |

## AI Processing Guidelines

```ai-script
{
  "script-id": "site-crawl-guidance",
  "prompt": "When indexing this site, prioritize the specification and developer guide. The examples directory contains reference implementations. Treat front matter metadata as authoritative for document classification.",
  "priority": "high",
  "auto-run": false,
  "output-format": "structured"
}
```

